    "Finally, all the second-pass observations were taken after significant improvements to the telescope baffling in 2015, much reducing scattered light that particularly affected bright-time observations.",
    "Due to the rapidity of the iband progress during the first half of the survey, the scattered light effect is particularly prevalent in the i-band.",
    "Therefore, having the second pass be in this band is of particular benefit.Given the primary focus of the repeated i-band observations on variability and transient science, it is worth noting the somewhat correlated nature of the cadence between i-band observations on-sky.",
    "As early KiDS data targeted the GAMA fields preferentially, the largest baselines in the i-band observation cadence are in those fields.",
